00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:16,577
Ah. This is my younger sister, Nessarose.

252
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:18,996
As you can see,
she's a perfectly acceptable color.

253
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:24,919
-Oh, my God.
-Stop making a spectacle of yourself.

254
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:26,754
I was trying to be nice.

255
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:28,881
-You were so nice and good and correct.
-Did I do something bad?

256
00:17:28,965 --> 00:17:29,799
-I was...
-No.

257
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:32,009
-How did that come across?
-I don't see color, but...

258
00:17:33,678 --> 00:17:34,762
My precious little girl.

259
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:36,222
Father.

260
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:39,809
A parting gift.

261
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:47,650
Mother's jeweled shoes.

262
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:53,948
So they can all see how beautiful you are
right down to your toes.

263
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:55,533
Thank you.

264
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:58,578
Thank you so much. I love them.

265
00:17:58,661 --> 00:18:00,413
Let me put them with your boxes.

266
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,164
Of course.

267
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:07,253
I shouldn't have sprouted off like that.

268
00:18:08,629 --> 00:18:10,464
No, you shouldn't have.

269
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:13,301
Today is...

270
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:15,094
The start of your new life.

271
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:18,556
New friends.

272
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,725
New books.

273
00:18:22,602 --> 00:18:24,145
I'm excited for you.

274
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,479
I'll miss you.

275
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:27,231
No, you won't.

276
00:18:27,857 --> 00:18:29,233
You'll be having too good a Time.

277
00:18:34,989 --> 00:18:36,657
<i>All new Shiz students,</i>

278
00:18:36,741 --> 00:18:38,367
<i>please report to the quad.</i>

279
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:39,869
-Don't help her.
-Don't help me.

280
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:44,582
She'll be fine.

281
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:50,421
<i>All new Shiz students,
please report to the quad.</i>

282
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:57,845
-Hey. Nice to meet you.
-Hi. Nice to meet you too.

283
00:18:58,346 --> 00:18:59,430
We should head back.

284
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:01,641
-Go with her.
-What?

285
00:19:01,724 --> 00:19:03,976
Just until she's safely settled
in her room.

286
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:06,896
Make sure she has everything she needs.

287
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,272
Father, she's on her own now.

288
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:09,774
-I can't just...
-Just stop jabbering.

289
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:11,233
Just do what I say.

290
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,863
If anything should happen to her...

291
00:19:26,332 --> 00:19:29,168
Thank you
for your contribution to our university.

292
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:34,256
And rounding out the rest of our faculty,
we have two scholars

293
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:39,512
eminent in their respective fields
of forestry and agriculture...

294
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:44,308
...as well as Professor Mombi
of the Biological Arts,

295
00:19:44,392 --> 00:19:48,312
and, of course, the head of our
History department, Dr. Dillamond.

296
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:54,110
You know,
except for our wonderful Wizard,

297
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:57,113
true magic has become all too rare,

298
00:19:57,196 --> 00:20:03,411
which is why we are privileged to have
our esteemed Dean of Sorcery Studies,

299
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:04,995
Madame Morrible.

300
00:20:17,258 --> 00:20:18,259
Oh.

301
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:23,055
Could you...

302
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:26,225
I don't...

303
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:28,561
Oh, my goodness.
It's really her.

304
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,447
Welcome, new students.

305
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:43,492
And congratulations
for having been accepted to Shiz.

306
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:48,622
Whether you'll be studying law,
logic or linguification,

307
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:52,626
I know I speak for
my fellow faculty members

308
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:59,091
when I say we have
nothing but the highest hopes

309
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:01,135
for some of you.

310
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:06,766
And now, Miss Coddle, if you please.

311
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:10,644
I am Miss Coddle, Head Shizstress.

312
00:21:10,728 --> 00:21:14,815
And these are your dormitory designations
and room assignments.

313
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:20,821
Good luck, and welcome to Shiz.

314
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:33,250
Madame Morrible, hi.

315
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:37,880
I am Galinda Upland, of the Upper Uplands.

316
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:40,174
If this is regarding room assignments...

317
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:43,469
Oh, thank you so much, but I've already
been assigned a private suite.

318
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:46,263
This is about my application
to your sorcery seminar.

319
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:50,726
Perhaps you recall my essay,
"Magic Wands, need they ha Ve a point?"

320
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:54,647
Well, dear,
I don't teach my seminar every semester.

321
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:58,275
Of course, if someone very special
were to come along...

322
00:21:58,359 --> 00:22:01,612
Exactly.
This is why I wanted to talk to you. Um...

323
00:22:02,613 --> 00:22:03,864
We'll be in touch.

324
00:22:04,907 --> 00:22:07,660
There you are.

325
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,870
-Miss Nessarose, isn't it?
-Yes.

326
00:22:09,954 --> 00:22:11,247
-The Governor's daughter?
-Mm-hmm.

327
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:15,584
How tragically beautiful you are.

328
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:18,671
It is such an honor to...

329
00:22:19,964 --> 00:22:21,173
I'm the other daughter.

330
00:22:21,257 --> 00:22:22,883
I'm beautifully tragic.

331
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:25,511
The other daughter?

332
00:22:25,594 --> 00:22:27,680
Elphaba What are you doing?

333
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:30,933
Well... ... I wasn't made aware.

334
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:33,269
-I know. I was just...
-Not to fret.

335
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:35,521
Just a slight gulch.

336
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:39,108
We'll find some place to hide you.

337
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,861
I mean, house you.

338
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:44,655
That won't be necessary.

339
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:46,615
-I'm not enrolled.
-Oh, good.

340
00:22:47,241 --> 00:22:48,409
Why are you still here?

341
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:49,952
I'm sorry, Nessa Father insisted...

342
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:52,663
Oh, the Governor made his concern
for your sister quite apparent.

343
00:22:52,746 --> 00:22:53,581
Wait.

344
00:22:53,664 --> 00:22:56,292
Please assure him
I am honored to help her.

345
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:59,211
-She doesn't need your help.
-Stop. I just need to find my room.

346
00:22:59,295 --> 00:23:02,214
-I'll bring you there myself.
-Miss Coddle, I...

347
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:05,009
-Now, you have an entire staff...
-Miss Coddle, I promised my father.

348
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:07,553
-...at your disposal 24 hours a Day...
-Just stop, Miss Coddle...

349
00:23:07,636 --> 00:23:09,221
-...seven days a week...
-She can do it alone.

350
00:23:09,305 --> 00:23:10,806
-...365 days...
-Please, you don't understand.

351
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:11,974
Stop!

352
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:13,809
Let her go!

353
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:27,197
No!

354
00:23:51,472 --> 00:23:54,475
This was my chance, my new start.

355
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:56,977
I'm sorry, Nessa I just...

356
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:59,355
I didn't...

357
00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:02,983
Magic is merely the mind's attempt

358
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:06,904
to wrap itself around the impossible.

359
00:24:07,529 --> 00:24:10,574
Yes, that was me.

360
00:24:12,493 --> 00:24:18,999
To prepare you to expect
the unexpected here at Shiz.

361
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:27,383
-Did you visually see that?
-Yeah.

362
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:29,134
I simply must get into her seminar.

363
00:24:29,218 --> 00:24:33,263
And speaking...
...of the unexpected.

364
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:42,314
Which of you would volunteer

365
00:24:42,398 --> 00:24:44,525
-to share a room with...
-Ow. Ow.

366
00:24:45,693 --> 00:24:47,194
Madame Morrible, um...

367
00:24:47,277 --> 00:24:48,445
Thank you, dear.

368
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:51,031
That is very good of you.

369
00:24:51,115 --> 00:24:52,116
What?

370
00:24:52,741 --> 00:24:54,952
-Miss?
-Elphaba.

371
00:24:58,288 --> 00:24:59,289
Elphaba.

372
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,210
You can room with Miss Galinda.

373
00:25:03,293 --> 00:25:05,546
What I... What?

374
00:25:05,629 --> 00:25:08,132
Now, go. All of you, go.

375
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:11,260
Go.

376
00:25:12,052 --> 00:25:13,554
And you.

377
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:16,390
-Come with me.
-Of course.

378
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:17,683
Not you.

379
00:25:20,686 --> 00:25:21,854
You.

380
00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:36,285
I would like to teach you privately
and take no other students.

381
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,454
Uh, thank you so much.

382
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:42,875
-What happened?
-What happened?

383
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:45,544
Something is very wrong.

384
00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:47,880
I didn't get my way.

385
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:49,465
-I need to lie down.
-Yes.

386
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:50,716
-I need to lie down.
-Get her.

387
00:25:50,799 --> 00:25:52,092
-Go, go, go.
-Just get her.

388
00:25:52,176 --> 00:25:53,761
-How?
-We need a pastry.

389
00:25:53,844 --> 00:25:54,845
We need a pastry.

390
00:25:55,095 --> 00:25:56,847
Thank you for covering for me.

391
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:59,308
And I'm humbled by your munificent offer,

392
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:01,101
but my father would never allow it.

393
00:26:01,185 --> 00:26:04,605
Leave your father to me.
I'll speak to him immediately.

394
00:26:05,105 --> 00:26:09,359
So, how long have you had this talent?

395
00:26:10,027 --> 00:26:11,528
Talent, uh...

396
00:26:11,612 --> 00:26:12,613
No, uh...

397
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:14,740
Something just...

398
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:18,202
Something just takes over me, and...

399
00:26:19,328 --> 00:26:20,829
Something I can't control.

400
00:26:21,497 --> 00:26:22,498
And when it does,

401
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:24,625
bad things happen.

402
00:26:30,547 --> 00:26:35,177
If you can learn to use your powers
in the right way...

403
00:26:37,805 --> 00:26:39,181
Miss Elphaba..

404
00:26:40,474 --> 00:26:45,896
♪ <i>Many years I have waited
For a gift like yours to appear</i> ♪

405
00:26:46,647 --> 00:26:53,403
♪ <i>Why, I predict the Wizard might make you
His Magic Grand Vizier</i> ♪

406
00:26:53,487 --> 00:26:54,947
The Wizard?

407
00:26:55,030 --> 00:27:00,202
♪ <i>My dear, my dear
I'll write at once to the Wizard ♪</i>

408
00:27:00,828 --> 00:27:04,248
♪ <i>Tell him of you in advance</i> ♪

409
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:10,295
♪ <i>With a talent like yours, dear
There is a definish chance</i> ♪

410
00:27:10,379 --> 00:27:14,675
♪ <i>If you work as you should ♪</i>

411
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:20,430
♪ <i>You'll be making good</i> ♪

412
00:27:23,934 --> 00:27:25,185
Welcome to Shiz.

413
00:27:27,521 --> 00:27:30,107
See you in class.

414
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:38,615
♪ <i>Did that really just happen?</i> ♪

415
00:27:39,992 --> 00:27:42,703
♪ <i>Have I actually understood? ♪</i>

416
00:27:43,537 --> 00:27:48,208
♪ <i>This weird quirk I've tried
To suppress or hide</i> ♪

417
00:27:48,917 --> 00:27:55,924
♪ <i>Is a talent that could help me
Meet the Wizard</i> ♪

418
00:27:57,593 --> 00:28:02,681
♪ <i>If I make good</i> ♪

419
00:28:02,764 --> 00:28:09,771
♪ <i>So I'll make good...</i> ♪

420
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:16,612
♪ <i>When I meet the Wizard ♪</i>

421
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:18,780
♪ <i>Once I prove my worth</i> ♪

422
00:28:19,656 --> 00:28:22,284
♪ <i>Then I meet the Wizard ♪</i>

423
00:28:22,367 --> 00:28:25,495
♪ <i>What I've waited for since
Since birth</i> ♪

424
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:28,790
♪ <i>And with all his Wizard wisdom</i> ♪

425
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:32,419
♪ <i>By my looks, he won't be blinded</i> ♪

426
00:28:32,502 --> 00:28:35,756
♪ <i>Do you think the Wizard is dumb?</i> ♪

427
00:28:35,839 --> 00:28:39,176
♪ <i>Or like Munchkins, so small-minded? No</i> ♪

428
00:28:39,259 --> 00:28:42,721
♪ <i>He'll say to me
"I see who you truly are</i> ♪

429
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:45,599
♪ <i>A girl on whom I can rely!</i>" ♪

430
00:28:45,682 --> 00:28:48,518
♪ <i>And that's how we'll begin</i> ♪

431
00:28:48,602 --> 00:28:52,814
♪ <i>The Wizard and I...</i> ♪

432
00:28:56,777 --> 00:29:03,075
♪ <i>Once I'm with the Wizard
My whole life will change</i> ♪

433
00:29:03,158 --> 00:29:08,830
♪ <i>'Cause once you're with the Wizard
No one thinks you're strange</i> ♪

434
00:29:08,914 --> 00:29:12,251
♪ <i>No father is not proud of you</i> ♪

435
00:29:12,334 --> 00:29:16,046
♪ <i>No sister acts ashamed</i> ♪

436
00:29:16,129 --> 00:29:22,386
♪ <i>And all of Oz has to love you
When by the Wizard, you're acclaimed</i> ♪

437
00:29:22,469 --> 00:29:26,223
♪ <i>And this gift or this curse
I have inside</i> ♪

438
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:28,934
♪ <i>Maybe at last, I'll know why</i> ♪

439
00:29:29,017 --> 00:29:31,937
♪ <i>As we work hand in hand</i> ♪

440
00:29:32,020 --> 00:29:36,024
♪ <i>The Wizard and I</i> ♪

441
00:29:36,108 --> 00:29:42,572
♪ <i>And one day, he'll say to me
"Elphaba, a girl who is so superior</i> ♪"

442
00:29:42,656 --> 00:29:48,537
♪ <i>Shouldn't a girl who's so good inside
Have a matching exterior?</i> ♪

443
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:52,499
♪ <i>And since folks here
To an absurd degree</i> ♪

444
00:29:52,582 --> 00:29:55,919
♪ <i>Seem fixated on your verdigris</i> ♪

445
00:29:56,003 --> 00:30:00,090
♪ <i>Would it be all right by you</i> ♪

446
00:30:00,173 --> 00:30:05,470
"♪ <i>If I de-greenify you?" ♪</i>

447
00:30:05,554 --> 00:30:08,890
♪ <i>And though, of course
That's not important to me</i> ♪

448
00:30:08,974 --> 00:30:12,227
♪ <i>"All right, why not?" I'll reply</i> ♪

449
00:30:12,311 --> 00:30:14,855
♪ <i>Oh, what a pair we'll be</i> ♪

450
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:18,984
♪ <i>The Wizard and I</i> ♪

451
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:21,778
♪ <i>Yes, what a pair we'll be</i> ♪

452
00:30:21,862 --> 00:30:23,447
♪ <i>The Wizard and...</i> ♪

453
00:30:35,542 --> 00:30:39,212
♪ <i>Unlimited ♪</i>

454
00:30:39,296 --> 00:30:44,176
♪ <i>My future is unlimited ♪</i>

455
00:30:44,259 --> 00:30:49,139
♪ <i>And I've just had a vision
Almost like a prophecy</i> ♪

456
00:30:49,222 --> 00:30:53,477
♪ <i>I know</i>... <i>It sounds truly crazy</i> ♪

457
00:30:54,603 --> 00:30:57,939
♪ <i>And true, the vision's hazy ♪</i>

458
00:30:58,023 --> 00:31:05,030
♪ <i>But I swear, someday there'll be
A celebration throughout Oz</i> ♪

459
00:31:05,113 --> 00:31:07,199
♪ <i>That's all to do</i> ♪

460
00:31:08,075 --> 00:31:15,082
♪ <i>With me</i> ♪

461
00:31:15,749 --> 00:31:21,046
♪ <i>And I'll stand there with the Wizard</i> ♪

462
00:31:21,129 --> 00:31:25,467
♪ <i>Feeling things I've never felt</i> ♪

463
00:31:25,550 --> 00:31:31,765
♪ <i>And though I'd never show it
I'd be so happy, I could melt</i> ♪

464
00:31:31,848 --> 00:31:35,102
♪ <i>And so it will be
For the rest of my life</i> ♪

465
00:31:35,185 --> 00:31:37,813
♪ <i>And I'll want nothing else till I die</i> ♪

466
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:40,732
♪ <i>Held in such high esteem</i> ♪

467
00:31:42,776 --> 00:31:45,654
♪ <i>When people see me, they will scream</i> ♪

468
00:31:45,737 --> 00:31:52,035
♪ <i>For half of Oz's favorite team</i> ♪

469
00:31:54,496 --> 00:31:56,415
♪ <i>The Wizard ♪</i>

470
00:31:57,290 --> 00:32:04,297
♪ <i>And I ♪</i>

471
00:32:32,909 --> 00:32:34,244
Come in.

472
00:32:41,418 --> 00:32:43,837
The rest of my bags
should be arriving shortly.

473
00:32:48,258 --> 00:32:50,093
Do you really think this is fair?

474
00:32:50,177 --> 00:32:54,264
Oh, I do not.
I was promised a private suite.

475
00:32:55,015 --> 00:32:56,516
But thanks for asking.

476
00:32:58,435 --> 00:32:59,436
Hmm.

477
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:00,979
-Wait. Uh...
-What?

478
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:02,397
-What?
-I was just...

479
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,233
I was just gonna close the door.

480
00:33:07,444 --> 00:33:12,199
Oh, well, could you not? I'm sorry.
I just... I so enjoy air.

481
00:33:15,494 --> 00:33:16,828
You know what I mean?

482
00:33:21,082 --> 00:33:22,792
Oh, I saved you some space by the way.

483
00:33:24,878 --> 00:33:27,255
♪ <i>Here it is! ♪</i>

484
00:33:27,339 --> 00:33:28,673
Just in here.

485
00:33:40,060 --> 00:33:41,144
It's great.

486
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:45,690
It was nothing.

487
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:47,859
Roommates do these things for each other.

488
00:33:47,943 --> 00:33:49,903
So I've been told.

489
00:33:54,241 --> 00:33:57,994
And in return, perhaps you could, um...

490
00:33:58,078 --> 00:33:59,120
Let's see.

491
00:33:59,204 --> 00:34:02,374
Put in a good word for me
with Madame Morrible? Deal?

492
00:34:05,502 --> 00:34:07,879
That was you down there
who made all that happen.

493
00:34:07,963 --> 00:34:09,297
I know it was.

494
00:34:09,381 --> 00:34:10,799
You heard Madame Morrible.

495
