01:25:31,960 --> 01:25:33,462
Why, Miss Elphaba..

1232
01:25:36,298 --> 01:25:37,549
Look at you.

1233
01:25:41,261 --> 01:25:42,512
You're beautiful.

1234
01:25:46,642 --> 01:25:47,809
I have to go.

1235
01:25:48,393 --> 01:25:49,519
Wha..

1236
01:25:56,568 --> 01:25:57,653
You're welcome.

1237
01:25:59,363 --> 01:26:01,490
Oh, hello.

1238
01:26:02,449 --> 01:26:04,201
Wow.

1239
01:26:06,828 --> 01:26:09,581
♪ <i>And tho' you protest</i> ♪

1240
01:26:10,457 --> 01:26:14,419
♪ <i>Your disinterest ♪</i>

1241
01:26:14,503 --> 01:26:21,510
♪ <i>I know clandestinely ♪</i>

1242
01:26:23,345 --> 01:26:25,430
♪ <i>You're gonna grin and bear it</i> ♪

1243
01:26:25,514 --> 01:26:28,016
♪ <i>Your newfound popularity</i> ♪

1244
01:26:29,267 --> 01:26:34,272
♪ <i>La, la, Ia, Ia</i> ♪

1245
01:26:34,356 --> 01:26:39,319
♪ <i>La, la, Ia, Ia</i> ♪

1246
01:26:39,403 --> 01:26:41,947
♪ <i>La, Ia</i> ♪

1247
01:26:47,119 --> 01:26:49,871
♪ <i>You'll be popular</i> ♪

1248
01:26:53,125 --> 01:27:00,132
♪ <i>Just not quite as popular as me</i> ♪

1249
01:27:10,016 --> 01:27:11,852
-Oh, hi, Elphaba.
-Hey.

1250
01:27:11,935 --> 01:27:13,186
Hey, Elphaba.

1251
01:27:19,943 --> 01:27:21,611
Toss, toss.

1252
01:27:22,279 --> 01:27:23,280
No.

1253
01:27:35,125 --> 01:27:36,543
You've been Galinda-fied.

1254
01:27:40,756 --> 01:27:43,049
You don't need to do that, you know.

1255
01:27:45,927 --> 01:27:47,763
Come on. Let's get to class.

1256
01:27:49,389 --> 01:27:51,641
-Dr. Dilly.
-Dr. Dilly, because you can't...

1257
01:27:51,725 --> 01:27:53,310
-Well, he calls me...
-Dr. Dillamond.

1258
01:27:53,393 --> 01:27:54,978
-It's not his fault.
-He needs to accept it.

1259
01:27:55,061 --> 01:27:56,438
He doesn't have upper front teeth.

1260
01:27:58,315 --> 01:28:00,525
Uh, Dr. Dillamond,
I picked you some poppies.

1261
01:28:00,609 --> 01:28:02,444
Not now, Miss Elphaba.

1262
01:28:03,028 --> 01:28:05,864
Please, everyone, take your seats.

1263
01:28:05,947 --> 01:28:08,366
I've something to say
and very little time.

1264
01:28:10,410 --> 01:28:12,245
My dear students,

1265
01:28:12,329 --> 01:28:15,540
this will be my last day here at Shiz.

1266
01:28:15,624 --> 01:28:19,294
You see,
animals are no longer permitted to teach.

1267
01:28:19,377 --> 01:28:20,378
What?

1268
01:28:20,462 --> 01:28:23,507
It's all right, Miss Elphaba
I'll be all right. I...

1269
01:28:31,389 --> 01:28:35,060
Students, remain calm, please.
There's no cause for alarm.

1270
01:28:35,143 --> 01:28:36,561
What is this? What's happening?

1271
01:28:36,645 --> 01:28:37,813
Come on, goat.

1272
01:28:40,106 --> 01:28:40,941
Hey!

1273
01:28:41,024 --> 01:28:42,025
You can't permit this.

1274
01:28:42,108 --> 01:28:44,194
Miss Elphaba,
I'm afraid it's out of our hands.

1275
01:28:44,277 --> 01:28:45,779
They can take away my job,

1276
01:28:45,862 --> 01:28:48,281
-but I shall continue speaking out!
-Dr. Dillamond.

1277
01:28:48,365 --> 01:28:52,369
Listen to me!
You're not being told the whole story!

1278
01:28:56,790 --> 01:28:59,000
Are we all just gonna sit here in silence?

1279
01:29:01,294 --> 01:29:04,714
That's quite enough, Miss Elphaba.

1280
01:29:06,800 --> 01:29:07,884
Take your seat.

1281
01:29:24,693 --> 01:29:25,694
Students...

1282
01:29:26,278 --> 01:29:27,279
Are you all right?

1283
01:29:27,362 --> 01:29:31,658
...your new history professor
has prepared a special presentation.

1284
01:29:47,799 --> 01:29:50,343
Good afternoon, students.

1285
01:29:53,513 --> 01:29:55,932
-Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.

1286
01:29:56,016 --> 01:29:57,684
In times such as these,

1287
01:29:57,767 --> 01:30:02,188
it behooves us all
not merely to study the past,

1288
01:30:02,272 --> 01:30:05,108
but to look to the future.

1289
01:30:09,112 --> 01:30:12,782
This is called a cage.

1290
01:30:18,705 --> 01:30:21,708
This remarkable innovation
is for the good of all Oz,

1291
01:30:21,791 --> 01:30:24,169
as well as for the animal's own good.
You see...

1292
01:30:24,252 --> 01:30:26,254
If it's so good, why is he trembling?

1293
01:30:31,051 --> 01:30:33,136
He's just happy to be here.

1294
01:30:34,888 --> 01:30:37,724
Now, one benefit
of caging an animal this young

1295
01:30:37,807 --> 01:30:40,644
is that in all likelihood,
he'll never learn to speak.

1296
01:30:41,269 --> 01:30:42,270
Oh, no.

1297
01:30:42,354 --> 01:30:45,148
The dimensions of the cage
will vary upon the size of the animal,

1298
01:30:45,231 --> 01:30:47,484
but the basic design remains the same.

1299
01:30:47,567 --> 01:30:49,194
Let me show you.

1300
01:30:52,238 --> 01:30:54,658
Can you imagine a world
where animals are kept in cages

1301
01:30:54,741 --> 01:30:56,326
and they never learn to speak?

1302
01:30:56,409 --> 01:30:58,036
This poor lion cub seems so frightened.

1303
01:30:58,745 --> 01:30:59,913
What are we gonna do?

1304
01:30:59,996 --> 01:31:01,581
Sorry, "we"?

1305
01:31:01,665 --> 01:31:04,501
Well, someone's got to do something.

1306
01:31:35,407 --> 01:31:38,201
Hey. Hey, hey. Hey, come here.

1307
01:31:40,745 --> 01:31:41,746
What is happening?

1308
01:31:43,039 --> 01:31:44,874
I don't know. I got mad and...

1309
01:31:47,127 --> 01:31:48,712
Fiyero, what are you doing?

1310
01:31:50,630 --> 01:31:52,465
Well, you coming?

1311
01:31:53,258 --> 01:31:54,384
Come on.

1312
01:31:59,514 --> 01:32:00,515
Look.

1313
01:32:00,598 --> 01:32:01,599
Come on.

1314
01:32:03,518 --> 01:32:05,186
Come, buddy. That's it.

1315
01:32:05,812 --> 01:32:08,440
-There we go. There we go.
-Yeah. All right.

1316
01:32:33,339 --> 01:32:34,632
What in the name of Oz?

1317
01:33:11,419 --> 01:33:13,213
I didn't mean to scare you.

1318
01:33:15,548 --> 01:33:18,384
Why is it you're always causing
some sort of commotion?

1319
01:33:18,468 --> 01:33:20,553
I don't cause commotions. I am one.

1320
01:33:20,637 --> 01:33:22,597
Yeah. Well, that's for sure.

1321
01:33:22,680 --> 01:33:25,683
So, you think I should just keep my
mouth shut? Is that what you're saying?

1322
01:33:25,767 --> 01:33:27,227
What? No. No, I'm saying...

1323
01:33:27,310 --> 01:33:29,020
-You think I wanna be this way?
-I...

1324
01:33:29,104 --> 01:33:31,231
-You think I wanna care this much?
-No, I mean...

1325
01:33:31,314 --> 01:33:33,274
I know my life would be much easier
if I didn't care, but...

1326
01:33:33,358 --> 01:33:35,110
Do you ever let anyone else talk?

1327
01:33:37,403 --> 01:33:38,404
Sorry.

1328
01:33:40,198 --> 01:33:42,117
-I was just...
-But can I just say one more thing?

1329
01:33:44,035 --> 01:33:45,870
You could've walked away back there.

1330
01:33:46,454 --> 01:33:47,455
So?

1331
01:33:47,539 --> 01:33:50,834
So no matter how shallow and self-absorbed
you pretend to be...

1332
01:33:50,917 --> 01:33:53,002
Uh, excuse me. There is no pretense here.

1333
01:33:53,086 --> 01:33:55,171
I happen to be genuinely self-absorbed
and deeply shallow.

1334
01:33:55,255 --> 01:33:57,215
Oh, please. No, you're not.

1335
01:33:57,298 --> 01:33:58,967
Otherwise, you wouldn't be so unhappy.

1336
01:34:08,476 --> 01:34:09,477
Fine.

1337
01:34:11,896 --> 01:34:14,232
-Well, if you don't want my help...
-No, I do.

1338
01:35:02,155 --> 01:35:03,907
What did you mean to do back there?

1339
01:35:06,659 --> 01:35:08,912
And why was I the only one
you didn't do it to?

1340
01:35:15,585 --> 01:35:16,586
You're bleeding.

1341
01:35:17,921 --> 01:35:18,922
Am I?

1342
01:35:19,714 --> 01:35:20,715
Mm-hmm.

1343
01:35:35,021 --> 01:35:36,022
There.

1344
01:35:41,027 --> 01:35:42,820
It must've scratched you.

1345
01:35:42,904 --> 01:35:43,905
Yeah.

1346
01:35:47,242 --> 01:35:49,369
Or maybe it scratched me or something.

1347
01:35:52,664 --> 01:35:53,790
I better get to safety.

1348
01:35:54,958 --> 01:35:56,417
-The cub.
-Mm-hmm.

1349
01:35:57,126 --> 01:35:58,336
-I better get the, uh...
-Of course.

1350
01:35:58,419 --> 01:36:00,171
-...the cub to safety.
-Mm-hmm.

1351
01:36:06,844 --> 01:36:07,845
Fiyero.

1352
01:36:18,773 --> 01:36:20,858
♪ <i>Hands touch</i> ♪

1353
01:36:23,820 --> 01:36:26,239
♪ <i>Eyes meet ♪</i>

1354
01:36:29,117 --> 01:36:32,287
♪ <i>Sudden silence</i> ♪

1355
01:36:33,037 --> 01:36:36,040
♪ <i>Sudden heat ♪</i>

1356
01:36:37,542 --> 01:36:44,382
♪ <i>Hearts leap in a giddy whirl ♪</i>

1357
01:36:45,091 --> 01:36:51,431
♪ <i>He could be that boy</i> ♪

1358
01:36:52,724 --> 01:36:58,438
♪ <i>But I'm not that girl</i> ♪

1359
01:36:59,147 --> 01:37:05,069
♪ <i>Don't dream too far ♪</i>

1360
01:37:05,778 --> 01:37:11,576
♪ <i>Don't lose sight of who you are</i> ♪

1361
01:37:11,659 --> 01:37:18,249
♪ <i>Don't remember that rush of joy</i> ♪

1362
01:37:18,333 --> 01:37:24,714
♪ <i>He could be that boy</i> ♪

1363
01:37:24,797 --> 01:37:30,094
♪ <i>I'm not that girl</i> ♪

1364
01:37:30,178 --> 01:37:34,223
♪ <i>Every so often we long to steal ♪</i>

1365
01:37:34,307 --> 01:37:38,561
♪ <i>To the land of what-might-have-been</i> ♪

1366
01:37:38,644 --> 01:37:43,608
♪ <i>But that doesn't soften
The ache we feel ♪</i>

1367
01:37:43,691 --> 01:37:49,364
♪ <i>When reality sets back in</i> ♪

1368
01:37:51,199 --> 01:37:57,330
♪ <i>Blithe smile, lithe limb</i> ♪

1369
01:37:57,955 --> 01:38:03,419
♪ <i>She who's winsome, she wins him</i> ♪

1370
01:38:04,128 --> 01:38:10,259
♪ <i>Gold hair with a gentle curl</i> ♪

1371
01:38:10,343 --> 01:38:15,973
♪ <i>That's the girl he chose</i> ♪

1372
01:38:16,599 --> 01:38:21,938
♪ <i>And heaven knows</i> ♪

1373
01:38:22,939 --> 01:38:28,778
♪ <i>I'm not that girl</i> ♪

1374
01:38:32,740 --> 01:38:33,741
Dearest!

1375
01:38:34,575 --> 01:38:36,702
Oh, my goodness. I was worried sick.

1376
01:38:38,329 --> 01:38:42,792
♪ <i>Don't wish, don't start ♪</i>

1377
01:38:44,585 --> 01:38:49,799
♪ <i>Wishing only wounds the heart ♪</i>

1378
01:38:50,591 --> 01:38:57,598
♪ <i>I wasn't born for the rose and pearl</i> ♪

1379
01:38:59,308 --> 01:39:05,314
♪ <i>There's a girl I know</i> ♪

1380
01:39:05,857 --> 01:39:10,194
♪ <i>He loves her so</i> ♪

1381
01:39:17,952 --> 01:39:24,375
♪ <i>I'm not that girl</i> ♪

1382
01:39:37,513 --> 01:39:39,098
<i>Miss Elphaba!</i>

1383
01:39:39,682 --> 01:39:40,766
<i>Come at once!</i>

1384
01:39:47,607 --> 01:39:48,774
There!

1385
01:39:51,319 --> 01:39:53,738
Elphie, you gotta get down there. Come on.

1386
01:39:58,326 --> 01:40:01,662
Miss Elphaba,
I finally heard back from the Wizard.

1387
01:40:01,746 --> 01:40:03,039
Look!

1388
01:40:10,421 --> 01:40:13,007
-Oh. Stop.
-I know.

1389
01:40:13,090 --> 01:40:15,843
I... I just cannot.

1390
01:40:27,271 --> 01:40:29,065
It's yours. Open it.

1391
01:40:35,863 --> 01:40:39,367
"His Royal Ozness,
the Wonderful Wizard of Oz..."

1392
01:40:40,785 --> 01:40:42,870
"...Summons you most ceremony-ishly

1393
01:40:42,954 --> 01:40:46,040
to his personal palace
in the Emerald City."

1394
01:40:46,123 --> 01:40:47,959
Uh, wait. Um, wait.

1395
01:40:48,543 --> 01:40:50,086
"This invitation is non-transferable."

1396
01:41:01,639 --> 01:41:04,517
This is your chance to make good.

1397
01:41:05,851 --> 01:41:09,105
Of course, you're going to have to
prove yourself first.

1398
01:41:09,188 --> 01:41:10,356
Prove myself?

1399
01:41:10,439 --> 01:41:12,024
Prove yourself worthy.

1400
01:41:12,108 --> 01:41:15,778
Dearie, this is the Wizard of Oz.

1401
01:41:16,571 --> 01:41:18,739
If he's gonna grant your heart's desire...

1402
01:41:18,823 --> 01:41:20,908
But prove myself how? I...

1403
01:41:21,701 --> 01:41:23,536
I'm not ready. It's too soon.

1404
01:41:23,619 --> 01:41:25,288
Don't be so pessi-mystical.

1405
01:41:25,371 --> 01:41:28,624
I, too, had to prove my powers
when I met the Wizard.

1406
01:41:29,208 --> 01:41:31,919
You'll find a way. I have faith in you.

1407
01:41:36,924 --> 01:41:40,136
Not to fret. Weather is my specialty.

1408
01:41:43,180 --> 01:41:44,682
Mustn't let you get wet.

1409
01:41:45,391 --> 01:41:46,934
Okay. I'll make a hand umbrella.

1410
01:41:47,018 --> 01:41:49,061
My hair. Thank you.

1411
01:41:57,486 --> 01:42:01,240
Not when you're on the cusp of greatness.

1412
01:42:31,687 --> 01:42:35,191
All aboard for the Emerald City!

1413
01:42:35,274 --> 01:42:37,902
Father, this is Boq,
the boy I wrote to you about.

1414
01:42:37,985 --> 01:42:41,989
Oh, yes. Governor Thropp,
good to meet you.

1415
01:42:42,073 --> 01:42:44,283
Oh, I've heard so much about you.

1416
01:42:44,367 --> 01:42:47,370
My Nessarose is very precious to me,

1417
01:42:47,453 --> 01:42:49,914
so you see you take good care of her.

1418
01:42:52,208 --> 01:42:53,542
I-I understand.

1419
01:42:54,669 --> 01:42:55,670
Good.

1420
01:42:57,546 --> 01:42:58,923
Elphie!

1421
01:42:59,006 --> 01:43:00,383
Elphie, the train is here.

1422
01:43:00,466 --> 01:43:03,469
And it came with the cutest little man
with a mustache. You gotta see him.

1423
01:43:03,552 --> 01:43:06,222
Oh, Elphie.
How will we manage without you?

1424
01:43:06,806 --> 01:43:08,224
You won't even notice I'm gone.

1425
01:43:08,307 --> 01:43:10,142
-Uh, you have Fiyero.
-Oh.

1426
01:43:10,226 --> 01:43:11,936
Um,
speaking of Fiyero, where is he?

1427
01:43:12,019 --> 01:43:14,021
Not that I expected him
to come and say goodbye, but...

1428
01:43:14,105 --> 01:43:16,524
I mean, we barely know each other.

1429
01:43:16,607 --> 01:43:18,776
Well, I barely know him anymore either.

1430
01:43:18,859 --> 01:43:20,277
He's been different.

1431
01:43:21,487 --> 01:43:23,489
He's distant and moodified.

1432
01:43:25,074 --> 01:43:26,784
And he's been thinking,

1433
01:43:26,867 --> 01:43:29,286
which really worries me.

1434
01:43:30,204 --> 01:43:32,039
It all started
the day Dr. Dillamond was fired.

1435
01:43:32,123 --> 01:43:34,667
I mean, who knew he cared so much
about that old goat?

1436
01:43:34,750 --> 01:43:37,336
Look. He did come.

1437
01:43:37,420 --> 01:43:38,587
Dearest.

1438
01:43:38,671 --> 01:43:41,674
We're over here, darling. Come.

1439
01:43:42,258 --> 01:43:44,301
Hi.

1440
01:43:45,177 --> 01:43:47,263
-Elphaba.
-Fiyero.

1441
01:43:49,140 --> 01:43:50,307
I'm happy for you.

1442
01:43:50,891 --> 01:43:51,892
Thank you.

1443
01:43:52,518 --> 01:43:55,354
Yes. We are both so happy.

1444
01:43:55,438 --> 01:43:58,733
-I've been thinking...
-Yeah. I heard.

1445
01:43:58,816 --> 01:44:01,694
...about the, uh, the lion cub
and Dr. Dillamond.

1446
01:44:03,612 --> 01:44:05,072
I think about that day a lot.

1447
01:44:06,240 --> 01:44:07,491
So do I.

1448
01:44:14,248 --> 01:44:15,416
Oh, me too.

1449
01:44:16,292 --> 01:44:18,627
Oh, me too. Me too. Mm-hmm.

1450
01:44:18,711 --> 01:44:20,296
I think about it constantly.

1451
01:44:20,796 --> 01:44:22,548
I mean, poor Dr. Dillamond.

1452
01:44:23,466 --> 01:44:25,342
It makes one want to...

1453
01:44:27,219 --> 01:44:28,554
...to take a stand.

1454
01:44:30,139 --> 01:44:32,391
In fact, excuse me.

1455
01:44:32,475 --> 01:44:36,061
Everyone. Please, I have an announcement.

1456
01:44:40,524 --> 01:44:42,610
I am changing my name.

1457
01:44:43,903 --> 01:44:44,904
-What?
-What?

1458
01:44:45,654 --> 01:44:47,281
-Your name?
-Yes.

1459
01:44:47,364 --> 01:44:49,116
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

1460
01:44:49,200 --> 01:44:53,954
Since Dr. Dillamond used to have his own
goat-like way of pronouncifying my name,

1461
01:44:54,038 --> 01:44:55,456
in solidarity

1462
01:44:55,539 --> 01:44:58,959
and in order to express my outrage,

1463
01:44:59,043 --> 01:45:02,755
I will henceforward be known
no longer as "Galinda,"

1464
01:45:04,256 --> 01:45:05,424
but simply...

1465
01:45:08,469 --> 01:45:09,595
Glinda.

1466
01:45:09,678 --> 01:45:12,097
Clapping!

1467
01:45:12,181 --> 01:45:14,266
-She's so good.
-Oh. She so is.

1468
01:45:14,350 --> 01:45:16,435
Such braverism.

1469
01:45:19,313 --> 01:45:20,147
Glinda!

1470
01:45:21,524 --> 01:45:25,027
Galinda no more,
Glinda henceforth!

1471
01:45:25,110 --> 01:45:26,862
Glinda, you're wonderful!

1472
01:45:29,406 --> 01:45:30,407
Glinda!

1473
01:45:44,380 --> 01:45:45,548
Good luck.

1474
01:45:53,013 --> 01:45:54,932
See? There.

1475
01:45:55,850 --> 01:45:57,184
What is that?

1476
01:45:57,268 --> 01:45:58,269
Don't be upset, Galinda.

1477
01:45:58,352 --> 01:46:01,188
It's "Glinda" now. Stupid.
I don't even know what made me say it.

1478
01:46:01,272 --> 01:46:02,565
It doesn't even matter what your name is.

1479
