02:01:44,172 --> 02:01:45,381
♪ <i>Or daughter ♪</i>

1712
02:01:46,883 --> 02:01:52,430
♪ <i>So Elphaba, I'd like to raise you high</i> ♪

1713
02:01:52,514 --> 02:01:59,521
♪ <i>'Cause I think everyone
Deserves the chance to fly ♪</i>

1714
02:02:04,317 --> 02:02:07,987
♪ <i>And helping you with your ascent</i> ♪

1715
02:02:08,071 --> 02:02:11,741
♪ <i>Allows me to feel so...</i> ♪

1716
02:02:13,785 --> 02:02:15,036
♪ <i>Parental ♪</i>

1717
02:02:18,581 --> 02:02:24,212
♪ <i>For I am...</i> ♪

1718
02:02:25,588 --> 02:02:29,926
♪ <i>A sentimental...</i> ♪

1719
02:02:33,137 --> 02:02:36,307
♪ <i>Man</i> ♪

1720
02:03:03,209 --> 02:03:05,545
That's enough of that. Okay.

1721
02:03:05,628 --> 02:03:07,463
Uh, uh, away with the moon.

1722
02:03:09,173 --> 02:03:10,717
-Huh.
-Is that...

1723
02:03:12,510 --> 02:03:14,387
-Oh, it is.
-It is.

1724
02:03:14,470 --> 02:03:17,432
Madame Morrible,
what are you doing here?

1725
02:03:18,016 --> 02:03:20,685
Oh, dearie.

1726
02:03:20,768 --> 02:03:22,729
I couldn't miss your big moment.

1727
02:03:28,401 --> 02:03:31,237
Neither could you, I see. Hmm.

1728
02:03:31,321 --> 02:03:32,322
I...

1729
02:03:41,706 --> 02:03:43,875
I don't believe it.

1730
02:03:44,500 --> 02:03:46,002
Is that the Grimmerie?

1731
02:03:46,836 --> 02:03:47,837
Yes.

1732
02:03:49,464 --> 02:03:54,260
That's the ancient book of wisdom,
thaumaturgy and enchantments.

1733
02:04:06,314 --> 02:04:07,649
Can I touch it?

1734
02:04:09,067 --> 02:04:10,068
No.

1735
02:04:11,861 --> 02:04:13,863
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

1736
02:04:13,947 --> 02:04:15,531
She may not be ready.

1737
02:04:15,615 --> 02:04:20,161
Casting a spell with the Grimmerie,
that's a mighty tall order.

1738
02:04:20,954 --> 02:04:22,246
I... You know, I should know.

1739
02:04:22,330 --> 02:04:24,290
You're right. We mustn't rush her.

1740
02:04:24,374 --> 02:04:26,250
Perhaps today has been too overwhelming.

1741
02:04:26,334 --> 02:04:27,669
No.

1742
02:04:27,752 --> 02:04:28,753
Please.

1743
02:04:29,879 --> 02:04:31,047
Let me try.

1744
02:04:32,256 --> 02:04:33,675
Let me prove myself.

1745
02:04:34,842 --> 02:04:35,677
Well...

1746
02:04:58,574 --> 02:05:00,743
Sweet Oz.

1747
02:05:00,827 --> 02:05:02,620
It opened for her.

1748
02:05:16,300 --> 02:05:18,803
So, which spell are you gonna start with?

1749
02:05:18,886 --> 02:05:21,556
We've been working on levitation.

1750
02:05:21,639 --> 02:05:25,309
Levitation? Oh, that's interesting.

1751
02:05:25,393 --> 02:05:28,896
Do you know that, um, Chistery here...

1752
02:05:29,605 --> 02:05:32,608
Ha.. Have you ladies met, uh, Ch-Chistery,

1753
02:05:32,692 --> 02:05:35,486
the leader of my... my Emerald Guards?

1754
02:05:36,070 --> 02:05:37,363
Pleased to meet you.

1755
02:05:37,447 --> 02:05:39,198
Uh, he'd hate to admit this.

1756
02:05:39,282 --> 02:05:40,908
Does not like talking about himself.

1757
02:05:41,659 --> 02:05:46,581
But he watches birds so longingly

1758
02:05:46,664 --> 02:05:48,207
every morning.

1759
02:05:48,291 --> 02:05:49,584
Birds?

1760
02:05:51,210 --> 02:05:53,755
-How can I help him? I don't...
-Elphie, look.

1761
02:06:01,095 --> 02:06:02,889
Are those words?

1762
02:06:05,433 --> 02:06:07,351
The lost language.

1763
02:06:07,435 --> 02:06:10,229
Our lost language of spells.

1764
02:06:10,813 --> 02:06:14,192
Don't be discouraged
if you can't decipher it.

1765
02:06:15,026 --> 02:06:19,030
Dearie, I, myself,
can only read a word or two,

1766
02:06:19,113 --> 02:06:20,782
and that took years.

1767
02:06:26,454 --> 02:06:28,122
-Oh, Elphie.
-Praise Oz.

1768
02:06:47,767 --> 02:06:48,935
What did I tell you?

1769
02:07:03,449 --> 02:07:04,700
Chistery, are you all right?

1770
02:07:04,784 --> 02:07:06,494
Chistery?

1771
02:07:09,831 --> 02:07:11,749
It's just the transition, dearie.

1772
02:07:11,833 --> 02:07:13,459
It's just the transition.

1773
02:07:24,011 --> 02:07:25,221
Oh.

1774
02:07:28,808 --> 02:07:30,143
But it's hurting him.

1775
02:07:31,310 --> 02:07:32,186
Chistery.

1776
02:07:32,270 --> 02:07:33,771
Don't bite. Don't bite.

1777
02:08:03,968 --> 02:08:05,344
Glory-osky.

1778
02:08:05,428 --> 02:08:08,431
You did it. You actually did it.

1779
02:08:19,483 --> 02:08:20,818
He's in pain.

1780
02:08:20,902 --> 02:08:22,403
Quick. How do I reverse it?

1781
02:08:22,486 --> 02:08:24,447
-Reverse...
-How do I reverse it?

1782
02:08:24,530 --> 02:08:27,074
A spell from the Grimmerie
can never be reversed.

1783
02:08:31,495 --> 02:08:34,165
Elphaba Elphaba.

1784
02:08:34,248 --> 02:08:35,625
No. No!

1785
02:08:53,142 --> 02:08:56,145
I knew she had the power. I told you.

1786
02:08:56,229 --> 02:08:57,897
Elphie, this is astoundifying.

1787
02:08:57,980 --> 02:09:00,233
It's just what we hoped for.
Eyes in the skies.

1788
02:09:00,316 --> 02:09:03,444
Yes. They'll make perfect spies.

1789
02:09:03,527 --> 02:09:04,528
Spies?

1790
02:09:06,364 --> 02:09:08,741
-Elphaba? Elphaba?
-Oh, uh, no. No. Uh...

1791
02:09:08,824 --> 02:09:11,118
Elphie? Elphie?

1792
02:09:13,162 --> 02:09:14,538
You're right. That's a very harsh word.

1793
02:09:14,622 --> 02:09:17,416
Oh, "scouts." What about "scouts"?
Because they're gonna be flying around Oz

1794
02:09:17,500 --> 02:09:19,252
reporting back
on any seditious animal activity...

1795
02:09:19,335 --> 02:09:21,128
Seditious animal activity?
What does that mean?

1796
02:09:21,212 --> 02:09:24,173
Elphie. I'm sure the Wizard
has a good reason.

1797
02:09:28,844 --> 02:09:29,971
It's you.

1798
02:09:31,430 --> 02:09:32,765
You're behind all of this.

1799
02:09:34,183 --> 02:09:36,560
You're the reason why
people are turning against the animals.

1800
02:09:36,644 --> 02:09:37,937
You... It's all because of you.

1801
02:09:39,605 --> 02:09:41,399
We're doing this to keep people safe.

1802
02:09:41,482 --> 02:09:43,401
All of Oz will benefit.

1803
02:09:43,985 --> 02:09:45,069
And you've known all along.

1804
02:09:46,779 --> 02:09:48,239
Since the day you met me.

1805
02:09:48,823 --> 02:09:51,492
You will benefit too, dearie.

1806
02:09:51,575 --> 02:09:53,744
-You must trust me.
-Don't. Don't.

1807
02:09:53,828 --> 02:09:55,246
El-Elphaba.

1808
02:09:55,329 --> 02:09:58,791
When I first got here, well,
there was discord.

1809
02:09:58,874 --> 02:10:00,084
There was discontent.

1810
02:10:00,167 --> 02:10:02,169
And back where I come from,

1811
02:10:02,253 --> 02:10:06,674
everybody knows that the best way
to bring folks together

1812
02:10:07,341 --> 02:10:10,803
is to give them a.. A real good enemy.

1813
02:10:11,804 --> 02:10:14,390
If you wanted s-spies,
why wouldn't you just...

1814
02:10:14,473 --> 02:10:16,434
Why wouldn't you just
make them yourself? You...

1815
02:10:25,609 --> 02:10:26,694
Elphaba.

1816
02:10:27,611 --> 02:10:28,696
Elphaba.

1817
02:10:29,447 --> 02:10:31,657
You are talking to the Wizard of Oz.

1818
02:10:34,243 --> 02:10:35,161
Read it.

1819
02:10:35,244 --> 02:10:37,204
Cast a spell.

1820
02:10:37,288 --> 02:10:39,081
Read it!

1821
02:10:39,165 --> 02:10:40,499
-Elphaba.
-Don't...

1822
02:10:45,296 --> 02:10:46,922
You can't, can you?

1823
02:10:49,258 --> 02:10:50,593
Can you?

1824
02:10:57,433 --> 02:10:58,976
That's why you need all of this.

1825
02:10:59,060 --> 02:11:02,772
And you need spies
and-and animals in cages and an enemy.

1826
02:11:02,855 --> 02:11:04,231
You...

1827
02:11:04,315 --> 02:11:05,816
You have no real power.

1828
02:11:06,609 --> 02:11:08,319
Exactly.

1829
02:11:08,402 --> 02:11:09,862
That's why I need you.

1830
02:11:09,945 --> 02:11:13,908
Think of your future, dearie.

1831
02:11:13,991 --> 02:11:15,201
Stay back.

1832
02:11:17,953 --> 02:11:19,372
Elphie, listen to them.

1833
02:11:21,582 --> 02:11:22,750
Please.

1834
02:11:23,417 --> 02:11:24,835
Good advice, young lady.

1835
02:11:24,919 --> 02:11:26,379
Listen, uh, Elphaba,

1836
02:11:26,462 --> 02:11:31,092
if you can pull this off
first crack out of the box...

1837
02:11:31,175 --> 02:11:35,096
Oh. Oh, my golly. I can't even imagine...

1838
02:11:35,179 --> 02:11:38,516
And I meant every word
about you having a home here.

1839
02:11:38,599 --> 02:11:40,976
It's gonna be you and me

1840
02:11:41,060 --> 02:11:44,146
and, hey, if it'd make you happy,

1841
02:11:44,230 --> 02:11:47,233
possibly your friend.

1842
02:11:47,316 --> 02:11:48,484
Really?

1843
02:11:49,860 --> 02:11:51,070
Why not?

1844
02:11:52,822 --> 02:11:54,365
No.

1845
02:11:56,409 --> 02:11:58,369
Elphaba.

1846
02:11:58,452 --> 02:12:01,163
You want to do yourself some good?
Get her back.

1847
02:12:04,417 --> 02:12:06,710
Elphie. Elphie!

1848
02:12:13,467 --> 02:12:14,468
Listen.

1849
02:12:19,223 --> 02:12:20,558
Listen!

1850
02:12:22,101 --> 02:12:24,895
If you want to keep your families safe,

1851
02:12:24,979 --> 02:12:27,731
you'll stay loyal to our Wizard.

1852
02:12:28,315 --> 02:12:31,193
She did this! The green one.

1853
02:12:31,277 --> 02:12:33,487
Don't let her get away!

1854
02:13:20,701 --> 02:13:22,203
Elphie, where are you going?

1855
02:13:22,286 --> 02:13:24,288
Elphie, what are you doing?

1856
02:13:24,371 --> 02:13:26,081
Oh. Oh! No.

1857
02:13:26,790 --> 02:13:29,293
Elphaba, please. Come back.
Let's just have a word with them.

1858
02:13:30,252 --> 02:13:31,670
Elphie. Elphie.

1859
02:13:31,754 --> 02:13:32,838
What are you doing?

1860
02:13:34,507 --> 02:13:35,591
Too much.

1861
02:13:38,636 --> 02:13:39,637
Take it.

1862
02:13:41,597 --> 02:13:43,641
Elphie! Oh! No...

1863
02:13:58,614 --> 02:14:03,035
Guards. Guards. Guards.

1864
02:14:03,118 --> 02:14:07,331
There's a fugitive at large
here in the palace.

1865
02:14:07,414 --> 02:14:10,834
Bring her to me.

1866
02:14:16,090 --> 02:14:17,091
Let's go.

1867
02:14:17,967 --> 02:14:20,261
-Elphaba, what are you doing?
-Just follow me. Follow me.

1868
02:14:20,344 --> 02:14:22,930
Where? What? Are you out of your mind?

1869
02:14:23,013 --> 02:14:24,682
Goodness, Elphaba,
you're being ridiculous.

1870
02:14:24,765 --> 02:14:26,934
-Just come on.
-Where are you going?

1871
02:14:27,810 --> 02:14:28,811
Up.

1872
02:14:32,398 --> 02:14:34,191
-They're in here!
-There she is! The green one.

1873
02:14:36,068 --> 02:14:38,153
-Get in quickly.
-Absolutely rid...

1874
02:14:40,906 --> 02:14:42,366
Quick. Jump.

1875
02:14:42,449 --> 02:14:44,159
Jump? Me, jump?

1876
02:14:44,243 --> 02:14:46,954
Quick. Jump, Glinda Jump now!

1877
02:14:47,037 --> 02:14:49,248
Slipping...

1878
02:14:49,331 --> 02:14:50,958
Just grab my hand. Come on!

1879
02:14:57,965 --> 02:14:59,967
Come on. Grab on!

1880
02:15:01,218 --> 02:15:02,845
Get off!

1881
02:15:03,429 --> 02:15:04,805
Give me my leg.

1882
02:15:05,681 --> 02:15:06,890
Give me my leg.

1883
02:15:10,019 --> 02:15:11,520
Everyone, wait!

1884
02:15:33,751 --> 02:15:35,336
-Move!
-Faster!

1885
02:15:35,419 --> 02:15:36,545
-Push!
-Help me with this!

1886
02:15:36,629 --> 02:15:37,963
Hey! No!

1887
02:15:43,969 --> 02:15:45,054
Oh, no, no.

1888
02:15:48,182 --> 02:15:49,516
Elphie, Elphie, Elphie.

1889
02:15:51,268 --> 02:15:52,728
Faster! Look out!

1890
02:16:02,988 --> 02:16:04,073
Quick! Get off.

1891
02:16:04,156 --> 02:16:05,532
Ow, ow!

1892
02:16:08,952 --> 02:16:10,371
Don't look back!

1893
02:16:10,454 --> 02:16:13,040
-Get out of the way! Move!
-Watch out!

1894
02:16:16,293 --> 02:16:19,755
This is not good.
This is not good. This is not good.

1895
02:16:19,838 --> 02:16:21,173
Elphie.

1896
02:16:21,256 --> 02:16:22,341
Elphie!

1897
02:16:22,925 --> 02:16:25,260
Calm down.
You have got to let him explain.

1898
02:16:25,344 --> 02:16:26,512
Over my dead body.

1899
02:16:27,221 --> 02:16:28,806
This is everything you've dreamed of.

1900
02:16:36,146 --> 02:16:39,358
Elphaba, this is so much bigger than us.

1901
02:16:39,441 --> 02:16:41,485
Why couldn't you have stayed calm
for once,

1902
02:16:41,568 --> 02:16:43,445
instead of flying off the handle?

1903
02:16:43,529 --> 02:16:44,822
I hope you're happy!

1904
02:16:44,905 --> 02:16:46,240
♪ <i>I hope you're happy now</i> ♪

1905
02:16:46,323 --> 02:16:49,326
♪ <i>I hope you're happy how
You hurt your cause forever</i> ♪

1906
02:16:49,410 --> 02:16:51,495
♪ <i>I hope you think you're clever</i> ♪

1907
02:16:51,578 --> 02:16:52,454
I hope you're happy.

1908
02:16:53,038 --> 02:16:54,415
♪ <i>I hope you're happy too</i> ♪

1909
02:16:54,498 --> 02:16:57,960
♪ <i>I hope you're proud how you
Would grovel in submission</i> ♪

1910
02:16:58,043 --> 02:17:00,462
♪ <i>To feed your own ambition</i> ♪

1911
02:17:00,546 --> 02:17:04,967
♪ <i>So though I can't imagine how</i> ♪

1912
02:17:05,050 --> 02:17:07,678
♪ <i>I hope you're happy ♪</i>

1913
02:17:08,262 --> 02:17:12,641
♪ <i>Right now</i> ♪

1914
02:17:12,725 --> 02:17:14,977
<i>Citizens of Oz,</i>

1915
02:17:15,060 --> 02:17:20,858
there is an enemy who must be found
and captured.

1916
02:17:20,941 --> 02:17:24,194
<i>Believe nothing she says.</i>

1917
02:17:24,278 --> 02:17:27,573
She has stolen our Grimmerie.

1918
02:17:28,157 --> 02:17:30,909
<i>She is evil,</i>

1919
02:17:30,993 --> 02:17:36,582
<i>responsible for the mutilation
of these poor, innocent monkeys.</i>

1920
02:17:36,665 --> 02:17:37,750
Oh, no.

1921
02:17:37,833 --> 02:17:41,044
<i>Her green skin</i>

1922
02:17:41,128 --> 02:17:46,884
<i>is but an outward manifestorium
of her twisted nature.</i>

1923
02:17:48,343 --> 02:17:50,888
<i>This distortion,</i>

1924
02:17:50,971 --> 02:17:53,891
<i>this repulsion,</i>

1925
02:17:53,974 --> 02:17:55,309
<i>this...</i>

1926
02:17:56,977 --> 02:18:00,063
<i>Wicked Witch.</i>

1927
02:18:15,746 --> 02:18:17,456
Don't be afraid.

1928
02:18:20,167 --> 02:18:21,376
I'm not afraid.

1929
02:18:24,171 --> 02:18:26,215
It's the Wizard
who should be afraid of me.

1930
02:18:29,718 --> 02:18:30,761
Elphie, listen to me.

1931
02:18:31,845 --> 02:18:35,140
Listen to me. Just...
Just say you're sorry.

1932
02:18:36,600 --> 02:18:40,854
♪ <i>You can still be with the Wizard</i> ♪

1933
02:18:40,938 --> 02:18:45,651
♪ <i>What you've worked and waited for</i> ♪

1934
02:18:45,734 --> 02:18:51,365
♪ <i>You can have all you ever wanted ♪</i>

1935
02:18:55,160 --> 02:18:56,328
I know.

1936
02:18:58,413 --> 02:19:00,457
♪ <i>But I don't want it ♪</i>

1937
02:19:02,459 --> 02:19:03,544
No.

1938
02:19:04,628 --> 02:19:07,923
♪ <i>I can't want it</i> ♪

1939
02:19:09,466 --> 02:19:16,348
♪ <i>Anymore</i> ♪

1940
02:19:21,436 --> 02:19:26,149
♪ <i>Something has changed within me</i> ♪

1941
02:19:28,193 --> 02:19:31,572
♪ <i>Something is not the same</i> ♪

1942
02:19:33,448 --> 02:19:38,495
♪ <i>I'm through with playing by the rules</i> ♪

1943
02:19:38,579 --> 02:19:42,374
♪ <i>Of someone else's game</i> ♪

1944
02:19:43,417 --> 02:19:46,670
♪ <i>Too late for second-guessing</i> ♪

1945
02:19:47,504 --> 02:19:52,509
♪ <i>Too late to go back to sleep</i> ♪

1946
02:19:52,593 --> 02:19:56,680
♪ <i>It's time to trust my instincts</i> ♪

1947
02:19:56,763 --> 02:19:59,933
♪ <i>Close my eyes...</i> ♪

1948
02:20:03,103 --> 02:20:05,814
♪ <i>And leap</i> ♪

1949
02:20:05,898 --> 02:20:11,862
♪ <i>It's time to try defying gravity ♪</i>

1950
02:20:11,945 --> 02:20:17,993
♪ <i>I think I'll try defying gravity ♪</i>

1951
02:20:18,076 --> 02:20:21,330
♪ <i>And you can't pull me down</i> ♪

1952
02:20:21,413 --> 02:20:26,251
♪ <i>Can't I make you understand
You're having delusions of grandeur?</i> ♪

1953
02:20:26,335 --> 02:20:29,379
♪ <i>I'm through accepting limits</i> ♪

1954
02:20:29,963 --> 02:20:32,299
♪ <i>'Cause someone says they're so</i> ♪

1955
02:20:33,050 --> 02:20:35,385
♪ <i>Some things I cannot change</i> ♪

1956
02:20:35,469 --> 02:20:39,306
♪ <i>But till I try, I'll never know</i> ♪

1957
02:20:39,389 --> 02:20:42,142
♪ <i>Too long I've been afraid of ♪</i>

1958
02:20:42,225 --> 02:20:45,687
♪ <i>Losing love I guess I've lost</i> ♪

1959
02:20:45,771 --> 02:20:47,522
♪ <i>Well, if that's love</i> ♪

1960
02:20:47,606 --> 02:20:52,110
♪ <i>It comes at much too high a cost ♪</i>

1961
02:20:52,194 --> 02:20:58,408
♪ <i>I'd sooner buy defying gravity</i> ♪

1962
02:20:58,492 --> 02:21:04,206
♪ <i>Kiss me goodbye, I'm defying gravity ♪</i>

1963
02:21:04,289 --> 02:21:09,336
♪ <i>And you can't pull me down</i> ♪

1964
02:21:09,419 --> 02:21:11,797
-They're up there!
-You two! Come down!

1965
02:21:14,925 --> 02:21:17,427
Elphie, what are you doing?

1966
02:21:17,511 --> 02:21:18,595
Elphaba, please.

1967
02:21:19,846 --> 02:21:21,515
Listen to me. Stop.

1968
02:21:25,268 --> 02:21:27,646
Not that hideoteous
levitation spell. Elphaba, please.

1969
02:21:27,729 --> 02:21:30,148
You don't know what you're doing
with that. Please.

1970
02:21:30,232 --> 02:21:33,235
Stop! Stop!

1971
02:21:33,318 --> 02:21:34,945
Stop!

1972
02:21:40,742 --> 02:21:41,785
Well...

1973
02:21:44,538 --> 02:21:45,789
where are your wings?

1974
02:21:49,459 --> 02:21:52,295
Maybe you're not as powerful
as you think you are.

1975
02:22:06,560 --> 02:22:07,978
Sweet Oz.

1976
02:22:53,398 --> 02:22:54,399
Charge!

1977
02:22:54,483 --> 02:22:55,442
Heave!

1978
02:22:59,112 --> 02:23:00,113
Quickly.

1979
02:23:01,907 --> 02:23:04,034
-Get on.
-What?

1980
02:23:04,117 --> 02:23:05,368
Heave!

1981
02:23:05,452 --> 02:23:06,453
Heave!

1982
02:23:06,995 --> 02:23:08,121
Heave!

1983
02:23:08,914 --> 02:23:10,540
Come with me.

1984
02:23:10,624 --> 02:23:13,710
Think of what we could do together.

1985
02:23:16,838 --> 02:23:20,509
♪ <i>Unlimited ♪</i>

1986
02:23:20,592 --> 02:23:25,514
♪ <i>Together we're unlimited ♪</i>

1987
02:23:25,597 --> 02:23:30,310
♪ <i>Together we'll be the greatest team
There's ever been</i> ♪

1988
02:23:30,393 --> 02:23:32,395
♪ <i>Glinda</i> ♪

1989
02:23:32,479 --> 02:23:35,190
♪ <i>Dreams the way we planned 'em</i> ♪

1990
02:23:35,774 --> 02:23:38,735
♪ <i>If we work in tandem</i> ♪

1991
02:23:38,819 --> 02:23:43,573
♪ <i>There's no fight we cannot win</i> ♪

1992
02:23:43,657 --> 02:23:50,539
♪ <i>Just you and I defying gravity</i> ♪

1993
02:23:50,622 --> 02:23:56,711
♪ <i>With you and I defying gravity ♪</i>

1994
02:23:56,795 --> 02:24:01,633
♪ <i>They'll never bring us down</i> ♪

1995
02:24:05,303 --> 02:24:06,638
Are you coming?

1996
02:24:20,861 --> 02:24:22,362
Elphie, you're trembling.

1997
02:24:42,090 --> 02:24:43,091
Hmm.

1998
02:24:44,176 --> 02:24:45,177
Here.

1999
02:24:46,386 --> 02:24:48,597
Put this around you.

2000
02:25:49,699 --> 02:25:51,660
♪ <i>I hope you're happy ♪</i>

2001
02:25:53,286 --> 02:25:56,039
♪ <i>Now that you're choosing this</i> ♪

2002
02:25:56,122 --> 02:25:57,290
You too.

2003
02:25:58,166 --> 02:26:00,669
♪ <i>I hope it brings you bliss</i> ♪

2004
02:26:00,752 --> 02:26:03,129
♪ <i>I really hope you get it</i> ♪

2005
02:26:03,213 --> 02:26:06,383
♪ <i>And you don't live to regret it ♪</i>

2006
02:26:06,466 --> 02:26:13,139
♪ <i>I hope you're happy in the end</i> ♪

2007
02:26:13,223 --> 02:26:16,393
♪ <i>I hope you're happy ♪</i>

2008
02:26:16,977 --> 02:26:21,982
♪ <i>My friend ♪</i>

2009
02:26:24,484 --> 02:26:25,527
Move!

2010
02:26:25,610 --> 02:26:26,653
-There they are!
-Get them!

2011
02:26:30,448 --> 02:26:31,449
Get her!

2012
02:26:31,533 --> 02:26:33,034
No. Leave her alone.

2013
02:26:33,118 --> 02:26:35,245
-She hasn't done anything wrong.
-Get away from me.

2014
02:26:35,328 --> 02:26:36,621
-No!
-Catch them now!

2015
02:26:36,705 --> 02:26:37,872
Elphie!

2016
02:26:39,874 --> 02:26:42,168
No! Back off. Back off!

2017
02:26:42,252 --> 02:26:44,129
-Elphie! Elphie, stop, no!
-I'm the one you want.

2018
02:26:44,212 --> 02:26:46,298
-I'm the one you want! It's me!
-No!

2019
02:26:47,799 --> 02:26:49,342
It's me!

2020
02:26:59,477 --> 02:27:02,439
-<i>What have you done this time?</i>
<i>-Elphaba Thropp, green on top.</i>

2021
02:27:02,522 --> 02:27:05,150
<i>Someone run and tell her
that everyone can smell her.</i>

2022
02:27:05,233 --> 02:27:07,694
<i>Just stop jabbering. Just do what I say.</i>

2023
02:27:08,194 --> 02:27:11,823
<i>Think of your future, dearie.</i>

2024
02:27:11,906 --> 02:27:13,658
<i>Take it away!</i>

2025
02:27:46,983 --> 02:27:51,237
♪ <i>It's me! ♪</i>

2026
02:27:51,321 --> 02:27:54,366
♪ <i>So if you care to find me</i> ♪

2027
02:27:54,449 --> 02:27:57,494
♪ <i>Look to the western sky! ♪</i>

2028
02:27:57,577 --> 02:27:59,954
♪ <i>As someone told me lately..</i> ♪

2029
02:28:00,038 --> 02:28:05,627
♪ <i>"Ev'ryone deserves the chance to fly" ♪</i>

2030
02:28:05,710 --> 02:28:08,463
♪ <i>And if I'm flying solo</i> ♪

2031
02:28:08,546 --> 02:28:11,383
♪ <i>At least I'm flying free</i> ♪

2032
02:28:11,466 --> 02:28:14,094
♪ <i>To those who'd ground me</i> ♪

2033
02:28:14,177 --> 02:28:18,181
♪ <i>Take a message back from me</i> ♪

2034
02:28:18,264 --> 02:28:24,020
♪ <i>Tell them how I am defying gravity ♪</i>

2035
02:28:24,687 --> 02:28:29,984
♪ <i>I'm flying high, defying gravity ♪</i>

2036
02:28:30,068 --> 02:28:35,323
♪ <i>And soon, I'll match them in renown</i> ♪

2037
02:28:46,668 --> 02:28:52,424
♪ <i>Unlimited ♪</i>

2038
02:28:53,007 --> 02:28:54,759
<i>Citizens of Oz,</i>

2039
02:28:55,677 --> 02:29:00,598
<i>there is an enemy who must be found
and captured.</i>

2040
02:29:02,851 --> 02:29:05,395
<i>Believe nothing she says.</i>

2041
02:29:05,478 --> 02:29:07,981
<i>She has stolen our Grimmerie.</i>

2042
02:29:08,064 --> 02:29:08,940
Governor?

2043
02:29:09,023 --> 02:29:11,276
<i>She is evil.</i>

2044
02:29:12,110 --> 02:29:17,490
♪ <i>Unlimited ♪</i>

2045
02:29:20,243 --> 02:29:22,454
<i>Her green skin...</i>

2046
02:29:23,204 --> 02:29:28,418
<i>is but an outward manifestorium
of her twisted nature.</i>

2047
02:29:29,961 --> 02:29:32,255
<i>This distortion,</i>

2048
02:29:32,338 --> 02:29:35,216
<i>this repulsion,</i>

2049
02:29:35,300 --> 02:29:36,426
<i>-this...</i>
-Come on!

2050
02:29:36,509 --> 02:29:38,970
♪ <i>Unlimited ♪</i>

2051
02:29:39,053 --> 02:29:41,556
<i>... Wicked Witch.</i>

2052
02:29:45,435 --> 02:29:48,354
♪ <i>And nobody in all of Oz</i> ♪

2053
02:29:49,397 --> 02:29:53,234
♪ <i>No Wizard that there is or was</i> ♪

2054
02:29:53,318 --> 02:29:57,530
♪ <i>Is ever gonna bring</i> ♪

2055
02:29:58,114 --> 02:30:00,575
♪ <i>Me down! ♪</i>

2056
02:30:00,658 --> 02:30:05,872
-♪ <i>I hope you're happy</i> ♪
-♪ <i>Look at her! She's Wicked! Kill her!</i> ♪

2057
02:30:05,955 --> 02:30:09,334
-♪ <i>Bring me down</i> ♪
-♪ <i>No one mourns the Wicked ♪</i>

2058
02:30:09,417 --> 02:30:15,340
♪ <i>So we've got to bring her...</i> ♪

2059
02:30:22,764 --> 02:30:29,729
♪ <i>Down! ♪</i>

2060
02:30:36,945 --> 02:30:43,243
♪ <i>Down! ♪</i>

